# Mastery memory lives here.
#
# One file per concept, named after a stable slug of the concept id.
# Schema (YAML front-matter + notes):
#
# ---
# concept_id: <slug>
# domain: <domain-slug>
# path_node: <learning-plan-node-id>
# prerequisites: [<concept_id>, ...]
# bloom_reached: remember | understand | apply | analyze | evaluate | create
# mastery: 0.0-1.0          # latest estimated mastery
# confidence_band: low | medium | high
# stability: <float>        # FSRS stability — how long before memory fades
# difficulty: <float>       # FSRS difficulty (0-10)
# retrievability: 0.0-1.0   # probability of correct recall now
# last_review: <ISO-8601>
# next_review: <ISO-8601>
# review_history:
#   - {ts: ..., rating: 1-4, response_ms: <int>, format: quiz|dialogue}
# misconceptions: [<free-text>]
# ---
#
# Free-form notes below the frontmatter — what the student has asked, where
# they got stuck, which analogies landed, which didn't.
